Good-faith reliance notice (added by the v3.x fork maintainer)

At the time this fork was created and published (April 2026), the upstream
repository at github.com/sbraind/excel-mcp-server did not contain a LICENSE
file. However, the upstream project unambiguously declared its license as
MIT and explicitly invited derivative work, in three binding places:

  1. The "license" field in upstream package.json:  "license": "MIT"
  2. The MIT badge in upstream README.md
  3. The upstream README "License" section reads:
        "MIT - See LICENSE for details."
     and the "Contributing" section explicitly invites forks:
        "Contributions are welcome! ... Fork the repository ..."

This fork was created in good-faith reliance on those declarations.
The fact that the LICENSE file referenced in the README does not actually
exist on disk appears to be an upstream documentation bug, not a
withdrawal of the license grant. The
upstream author is credited prominently in:

  - The Copyright line above
  - README.md (top-of-file attribution callout + Links section)
  - package.json contributors[] field

If the upstream author wishes to clarify, restrict, or add additional
conditions to the license terms, the maintainer of this fork commits to
honoring those terms promptly. Please open an issue at
https://github.com/emilio-S03/Excel-MCP-Server/issues to make contact.
